    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"well-known patterns\" you're asking about are often presented in ways that conflate correlation with causation, which is a common trap in this field. While socioeconomic factors like income are clearly major drivers, some studies have historically drawn lines suggesting inherent differences based on ethnicity. To truly separate the variance, you'd need to look at highly controlled, often controversial, datasets that attempt to isolate racial effects from environmental ones.",
