    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "could you name some of those controversial studies or the specific types of findings they report? specifically i'm looking for research that tries to account for the \"residual\" variance—the part that isn't explained by poverty or education—to see if the data actually supports any kind of demographic difference in behavioral tendencies or if it's all just noise in the socioeconomic variables.",
